The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Taylorsville had a population of 123. The population density was {{convert|37.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Taylorsville was 103 (83.7%) [[White Americans|White]], 11 (8.9%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], and 9 (7.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 9 persons (7.3%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Taylorsville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0678008 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 17, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 62 households, out of which 9 (14.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 29 (46.8%) were married-couple households, 3 (4.8%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 25 (40.3%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 5 (8.1%) had a male householder with no partner present. 29 households (46.8%) were one person, and 19 (30.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.98.<ref name=DP1/> There were 30 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (48.4% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Taylorsville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0678008 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 17, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 20 people (16.3%) under the age of 18, 8 people (6.5%) aged 18 to 24, 21 people (17.1%) aged 25 to 44, 41 people (33.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 33 people (26.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 56.8{{nbsp}}years. There were 60 males and 63 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 74 housing units at an average density of {{convert|22.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 62 (83.8%) were occupied. Of these, 50 (80.6%) were owner-occupied, and 12 (19.4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

